## Problem description

There are 7 types of goods (goods1 - goods7), 3 trucks (truck1, truck2, truck3), 3 markets (market1, market2, market3), 2 depots (depot1, depot2), and 4 possible levels (level0 - level3). All trucks have no goods loaded. All depots have no goods stored. The market market1 has 3 levels of goods of type goods1, 1 level of goods2, 3 levels of goods3, 2 levels of goods4, 2 levels of goods5, 3 levels of goods6 and 1 level of goods7 for sale. The market market2 has 1 level of goods of type goods2 and 1 level of goods4 for sale. The market market3 has 1 level of goods of type goods2 and 2 levels of goods7 for sale. No goods have been purchased yet at any market. The truck truck1 is at depot2, truck2 is at depot2 and truck3 is at depot1. The goal is to store 3 levels of goods of type goods1, 2 levels of goods2, 2 levels of goods3, 3 levels of goods4, 2 levels of goods5, 1 level of goods6 and 2 levels of goods7 at the depot.
